cs.SY, cs.CE, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, q-bio.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the design and implementation of feedback control strategies for a MIMO control system, the synthetic toggle switch. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses computational methods to simulate and validate the proposed control strategies. 
- q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods): The paper uses mathematical models to describe the behavior of the genetic toggle switch and the control strategies. 
- q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs): Although not directly related to tissues and organs, the synthetic toggle switch is a genetic circuit that can be used to control gene expression in cells, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
- q-bio.SC (Subcellular Processes): The synthetic toggle switch is a genetic circuit that operates at the subcellular level, making this sub-category also relevant.
